long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
This page will help you turn everyday numbers into Roman Numerals and vice-versa. 

The numeric system represented by Roman numerals originated in ancient Rome and remained the usual way of writing numbers throughout Europe well into the Late Middle Ages. Numbers in this system are represented by combinations of letters from the Latin alphabet. For more details on Roman Numerals visit https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman_numerals
